<2ND_LINE>PM-Raucous Party,0332</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Son Missing Since Destructive Party Returned to Family Home</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROLLING MEADOWS, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 20-year-old, developmentally
disabled man has been reunited with his parents, six days after he
disappeared following a weeklong party that inflicted $10,000
damage on his family's home, police said.
   Michael McConaghey ``is safe and sound. And his parents are very
happy,'' Deputy Police Chief Richard Hammer said Friday, announcing
the felony theft arrest of a 17-year-old girl accused of
instigating the blowout.
   McConaghey, who apparently fled out of fear for his parents'
anger, was detained at an Indiana truckstop Friday while trying to
hitch a ride to Nashville, Tenn., police said. His parents picked
him up hours later.
   Hammer said Lisa Wood, 17, of Wheaton apparently organized the
party that ran from March 29 until Sunday, while vacationing
parents Corinne and Wallace McConaghey had left the house in
Michael's care.
   Apparently, police said, Miss Wood contacted McConaghey after
hearing him on a Chicago radio station, saying he was lonely and
giving his telephone number on the air.
   Hammer said Miss Woods gave Michael beer during the week and
that the alcohol, mixed with medication he takes, made him pass
out. While Michael slept, Hammer said, Miss Woods entertained as
many as 100 people.
   When police arrived at the house Easter Sunday, Michael appeared
disoriented and told them he had fallen asleep. Michael then walked
off, and his parents had been looking for him ever since.
   Miss Wood was arrested on felony theft charges, accused of
stealing the McConagheys' car, which was found in a forest preserve
Monday, a day after neighbors called police to the family home and
questioned Michael.
   About $15,000 in property was stolen from the house in addition
to the damages, police said.
   Hammer said investigators are continuing to locate other people
who were at the party. So far, six teen-agers, including Miss
Woods, have been arrested and have posted bond.
</TEXT>
