<1ST_LINE>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     04-09 0432</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0442</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Thunderstorms Plague Central Plains While Spring Snow Persists</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   A cold front continues to bear down on the central Plains today,
bringing thunderstorms, fierce winds, rain and even some lingering
snow.
   Thunderstorms whipped through western Texas, Kansas and
southeast Nebraska Friday night with winds gusting to 72 mph in
parts of Kansas.
   In addition to the thunderstorms, the cold front brought rain to
eastern South Dakota and western Minnesota, and snow fell from
northeast Colorado into western Nebraska. Fort Collins, Colo.,
recorded two inches of snowfall Friday.
   Strong winds followed the cold front into the central high
Plains. In Colorado, northerly winds gusted to 64 mph at Trinidad
and 56 mph at Pueblo.
   Early today, showers were scattered along the middle Atlantic
coast; scattered rain or snow extended across western New York and
Pennsylvania. A few snow showers lingered over southern Montana and
western Wyoming, and skies were mostly clear west of the Rockies
and over the southeastern quarter of the country.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms over the
southern half of the Plains; showers from Minnesota into central
and eastern Nebraska; rain and snow from eastern North Dakota to
the Nebraska Panhandle; and showers over south Texas and northern
Maine.
   High temperatures will be in the 50, 60s or 70s across much of
the nation; in the 30s over much of Wyoming; in the 40s from
Colorado across the northern half of the Plains into northern
Minnesota, across New York and New England; in the 80s to around 90
over California, southern Arizona and southwest Texas; near 80 over
the lower half of the Mississippi Valley and the Gulf Coast region.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 11
degrees at Yellowstone Park, Wyo., to 78 degrees at Phoenix, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 51 fair; Boston 43 cloudy; Buffalo 37 showers;
Charleston, S.C. 57 fair; Cincinnati 40 fair; Cleveland 35 fair;
Detroit 34 fair; Miami 61 fair; New York 46 windy; Philadelphia 42
cloudy; Pittsburgh 40 partly cloudy; Portland, Maine, 44 cloudy;
Washington 45 rain.
   _Central: Bismarck 37 cloudy; Chicago 45 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
56 fair; Denver 32 snow; Des Moines 57 fair; Indianapolis 45 fair;
Kansas City 64 partly cloudy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 53 cloudy;
Nashville 46 fair; New Orleans 58 fair; St. Louis 56 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 55 fair; Anchorage 32 cloudy; Las Vegas 58
fair; Los Angeles 62 foggy; Phoenix 78 fair; Salt Lake City 32
fair; San Diego 62 cloudy; San Francisco 50 partly cloudy; Seattle
41 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 41 cloudy; Toronto 34 fair.
</TEXT>
