<HEAD>Supermarket Shelves Collapse, Injure Six</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRISBANE, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Several supermarket shelves collapsed
like giant dominoes Saturday, trapping customers and injuring six
people, police said.
   State emergency service volunteers were called in to help rescue
people buried under the shelving and groceries in the suburban
Brisbane store.
   The six injured were taken to a nearby hospital. All were
treated for minor injuries and discharged, police said.
   Police were investigating the cause of the accident.
