<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Pilecki,0139</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Former State College President Back on Fitchburg Faculty.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FITCHBURG, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Francis J. Pilecki, who stepped down as
Westfield State College president in the wake of allegations of
sexual misconduct, has returned to the faculty of Fitchburg State
College.
   Pilecki stepped down at Westfield after he was indicted in 1986
on charges of sexually assaulting two male students. He was found
innocent in one case and charges were dropped in the other after
settlement of a civil suit.
   Terry Zoulas, spokesman for the Massachusetts Board of Regents,
said Pilecki was entitled to his tenured professorship at Fitchburg
under terms of a collective bargaining agreement. Pilecki kept his
Fitchburg status when he took the Westfield job in 1979.
   The Boston Herald reported that Pilecki, 54, is ill and is on
extended sick leave.
