<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Salvador-Violence     04-09 0178</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Salvador-Violence,0183</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Salvadoran Rebels Kill 10 Soldiers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Leftist guerrillas attacked a
village Saturday in the province of Usulutan, killing 10 government
soldiers and injuring 20 others, military and civilian officials
said.
   The officials said members of the Farabundo Marti National
Liberation Front, an alliance of five rebel armies, attacked
government positions in Villa El Triunfo, 74 miles east of the
capital of San Salvador.
   The officials of the Sixth Infantry Brigade of Usulutan and
civilians in that region, all of whom demanded anonymity for
security reasons, said the rebels attacked the village early
Saturday.
   They destroyed two army tanks, set fire to the offices of a
state-run communications company and damaged four private houses,
the officials reported.
   The Armed Forces press office, meanwhile, reported that
government troops killed 20 rebels and injured 13 others in the
first week of April. Three soldiers died and 13 were wounded in the
fighting, it said.
   Leftist guerrillas have been fighting the U.S.-backed government
since 1979. The civil war has claimed an estimated 65,000 lives.
</TEXT>
