<1ST_LINE>r a AM-ToothlessEscapee     04-09 0223</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Toothless Escapee,0227</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Minnesota Escapee Captured in Apartment Complex</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A toothless inmate who escaped in
Minnesota while being escorted to a hospital to pick up his
dentures was captured Saturday by police and federal authorities in
his hometown of Columbus.
   Edward Lee Dugan, 34, who has federal convictions for mail fraud
and narcotics violations, was arrested without incident at an
apartment complex where his sister lives, U.S. Marshal Bob Obenour
said.
   Dugan had been held at the Ramsey County Adult Detention Center
in St. Paul, Minn., since March 22 and was being escorted to a
medical center when a gunman confronted the deputy escorting him
and ordered him to free Dugan.
   Dugan, who was a native of Columbus and had been a construction
worker, was handcuffed as he fled the hospital where his dentures
had been repaired. He left without picking up his dentures, but he
was wearing dentures when arrested Saturday, authorities said.
   No one was injured in the escape. The gunman who assisted in the
escape has not been identified.
   Dugan was originally convicted of mail fraud and was sentenced
to seven years at a federal correctional center in Rochester,
Minn., a federal prosecutor in Minneapolis said.
   Later, he pleaded guilty to smuggling marijuana into the prison
and received an eight-month consecutive sentence, federal officials
said.
  
</TEXT>
