<HEAD>James Brown's Wife Arrested On Drug Charges</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS last graf to UPDATE with two women released on bond.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>AUGUSTA, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Adrienne Lois Brown, estranged wife of soul
singer James Brown who accused her husband last week of trying to
kill her, was herself arrested Saturday and charged with possession
of a hallucinogenic drug, police said.
   Officer D.R. Brown of the Augusta Police Department said his
department had received information that Mrs. Brown was going to
receive a shipment of PCP from New York at Bush Field airport,
according to police reports.
   Brown and Detective T.C. Walker approached Mrs. Brown and
another woman, Ranell T. Wright, at the airport and confiscated
nasal spray bottles full of ``a brown, leafy substance'' mixed with
PCP, according to police reports.
   A cigarette Mrs. Brown apparently tried to hide from the police
also tested positive for PCP, police reports said.
   Last week Mrs. Brown, who has filed for divorce, accused her
husband of trying to kill her, and Brown was charged with assault
with intent to murder and aggravated assault and battery for the
incidents at Brown's Beech Island, S.C., home. She accused him of
beating her with a pipe and firing a gun at the car she was in.
   He turned himself in to Aiken County, S.C., authorities and was
released on Tuesday on $15,000 bond. He denied attacking her.
   Brown, who won a Grammy last year for ``Living in America,''
later left for a concert tour in Brazil.
   Mrs. Brown, 38, and Ms. Wright, 25, of New York each charged
with one felony count of possession of PCP. They were later
released on $1,550 cash bond apiece.
</TEXT>
