Irving's photograph. Police filed aggravated robbery charges, and
the case was scheduled to be heard Tuesday by a grand jury.
   Meanwhile, Irving pleaded guilty to the previous aggravated
robbery charge before the jury was seated. He was sentenced to six
years in prison.
   ``This is a small world,'' said court bailiff Bill West. ``I
love it.''
