<HEAD>Nine Florida Senate Pages Arrested On Alcohol Charges</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nine teen-age Florida Senate pages were
arrested after a deputy found them having an unsupervised beer
party at a motel, the Leon County Sheriff's Department said Friday.
   If convicted, the teen-agers face sentences of up to 60 days in
jail and fines of up to $500. Those arrested Thursday night range
from 16 to 18 years old, said sheriff's spokesman Dick Simpson.
Florida's legal drinking age is 21.
   The one 18-year-old will appear in adult court, while the others
will be handled through juvenile court, he said.
   Senate officials planned no discipline because they had finished
their week-long tour of duty Friday and the incident occurred after
work hours, said Senate Sergeant-at-Arms Wayne Todd.
   ``If they were drunk on the job it would be different,'' said
Todd. ``I don't think it's our responsibility to supervise them
after hours.''
